cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the application of linguistic features for detecting cognitive impairments, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a framework that involves neural networks, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, making cs.AI the second likely sub-category. The use of neural networks for learning low-dimensional representations and optimizing them iteratively indicates the involvement of machine learning (ML) techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves the use of consensus networks, which could be related to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the use of neural networks for optimization suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE).
